#week-title("Two", "Potency Testing & Materia Medica")

=== Core Teaching

The final test of the Plant Stone is its *potency*. This can be tested by
immersion: observing its effect when placed in the presence of another herb.
A completed Stone should exhibit a solid, attracting quality.

This week, you must also begin your *Materia Medica* notebook. This is a
permanent record documenting every preparation made in Year One: the herb, the
timing, the challenges encountered, and the final result. This document will be
your primary reference as you move into the water and mineral works.

=== Topics This Week

- Testing the Stone's quality
- Sourcing and formatting the Materia Medica notebook
- Transitioning from "Student" to "Practitioner"

#inner-work[
  *The World Card*

  Examine the Tarot card of *The World (Key 21)*. This represents the
  completed Magnum Opus. In our curriculum, it marks the end of the Tyro tier
  and the beginning of the Initiate tier.

  Meditate with this card. Contemplate the dancer in the centre. How does this
  image of completion relate to your own sense of achievement this year?
]

